race.comment: They'll go like the clappers in this. HOLY CROWN (13) is an honest type who has hit the top-four at her past five starts and will be rock-hard fit for this. Drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley and can get that well-deserved victory. ALL TOO LUCKY (4) is a winner over this six-furlong journey, gets 3kg off with the claim and maps ideally from gate three. Ticks a few boxes. BRAZEN SAILOR (9) will find this easier than recent Sunny Coast outings and gets the services of Wiggins in the saddle. Capable of sharp improvement. VICTORY'S GHOST (6) is a two-time winner around this circuit who could run a big race while fresh. Former NSW galloper SAINT CAYETANO (7) is having his first run for the new barn but looked to have some ability breaking the maiden status at Port Macquarie before the spell. Might be one at odds.
